external_knowledge:
- "Cumulative number of purchases" refers to the running total of purchases for customers with the same average spend;
- "Average spend" is calculated by averaging the prices of all items purchased by a customer;
- "Total purchases" is the count of all items bought by a customer.

- "Most valuable customer" refers to the customer with the highest total spent and, among those, the highest average rating;
- "Average rating" is calculated based on the ratings given by the customer in the `reviews` table;
- "Total spent" is the sum of the total prices of all orders placed by the customer.

- "size charts" refer to the standardized measurements used to determine the fit of clothing items;
- "preferences of those who wear them" refers to the size preferences of customers;
- The query aims to find the number of unique clothing types that are associated with size charts and customer size preferences.

sql:
SELECT brand_id, COUNT(clothing_item_id) AS num_clothing_items
FROM brands_clothing_items
GROUP BY brand_id;

external_knowledge:
- "wardrobe as diverse as a garden" refers to a wide variety of clothing types and items;
- "more than two different types of clothing" means the customer has purchased more than two distinct clothing types;
- "more than five purchases" indicates the customer has made more than five total purchases;
- "received recommendations for more than one type of clothing" means the customer has been recommended more than one distinct type of clothing.
